---
import Layout from "@/layouts/Layout.astro";
---

<Layout canonical="/">
    <main class="max-w-6xl mx-auto px-6 sm:px-12 py-16">
        <div class="flex flex-col md:flex-row md:gap-12 lg:gap-20">
            <div class="md:w-1/3 md:shrink-0">
                <div class="md:sticky md:top-12">
                    <img
                        src="/profile.jpeg"
                        alt="Jose Esparza"
                        class="w-full max-w-xs md:max-w-none mx-auto md:mx-0 rounded-sm"
                    />
                    <p class="text-xs text-[var(--color-text-faint)] mt-4 italic">
                        Eating soup
                    </p>
                </div>
            </div>

            <div
                class="md:w-2/3 md:pl-10 md:border-l md:border-[var(--color-border-light)] space-y-10 mt-12 md:mt-0"
            >
                <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-[var(--color-heading)]">
                    About
                </h2>

                <div class="space-y-6 text-[var(--color-text)] leading-relaxed">
                    <p>
                        I like owning a system from the first prototype to the
                        dashboards that watch it in production. As a Senior ML
                        Engineer, most of what I ship now is LLM systems: agentic
                        assistants with LangGraph and MCP, RAG over vector
                        databases, and fine-tuned Llama models for
                        domain-specific generation, plus the BI and observability
                        around them. I've worked across fintech, edtech, retail
                        and large enterprise.
                    </p>
                    <div>
                        <p>Recent builds:</p>
                        <ul class="space-y-2 mt-3">
                            <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
                                <span
                                    class="mt-2 w-1.5 h-1.5 rounded-full bg-[var(--color-dot)] shrink-0"
                                ></span>
                                <span>WhatsApp customer-support agents</span>
                            </li>
                            <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
                                <span
                                    class="mt-2 w-1.5 h-1.5 rounded-full bg-[var(--color-dot)] shrink-0"
                                ></span>
                                <span>Semantic search over a lesson catalog</span>
                            </li>
                            <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
                                <span
                                    class="mt-2 w-1.5 h-1.5 rounded-full bg-[var(--color-dot)] shrink-0"
                                ></span>
                                <span
                                    >A Llama-based lesson generator fine-tuned on
                                    expert-picked curriculum to preserve a
                                    specific technical-English voice</span
                                >
                            </li>
                            <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
                                <span
                                    class="mt-2 w-1.5 h-1.5 rounded-full bg-[var(--color-dot)] shrink-0"
                                ></span>
                                <span>High-volume retailer data ingestion</span>
                            </li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>
                    <p>
                        Earlier in my career I led a five-engineer data team
                        building AWS pipelines that ingested product-availability
                        data from Cencosud, Falabella and Walmart, and trained
                        default-risk models for fintech lenders. Before that I
                        engineered raw-material microservices for INDITEX,
                        refactored the Spanish Ministry of Justice's certificate
                        system to handle 500k+ records, and shipped a full-stack
                        risk platform for Barrick Gold. My{" "}
                        <a href="/resume.pdf" target="_blank">resume</a>{" "}
                        has the specifics.
                    </p>
                    <p>
                        I'm deep in the Julia open-source community. Google Summer
                        of Code 2023 funded my work on{" "}
                        <a
                            href="https://summerofcode.withgoogle.com/archive/2023/projects/iRxuzeGJ"
                            target="_blank"
                        >
                            empowering Julia-based Data Science with MLflow
                        </a>. I contribute to the{" "}
                        <a
                            href="https://alan-turing-institute.github.io/MLJ.jl/dev/"
                            target="_blank"
                        >
                            Machine Learning in Julia (MLJ)
                        </a>{" "}
                        framework and maintain{" "}
                        <a
                            href="https://github.com/JuliaAI/DearDiary.jl"
                            target="_blank"
                        >
                            DearDiary.jl
                        </a>{" "}
                        under the JuliaAI organization.
                    </p>
                    <p>
                        I hold a B.S. in Software Engineering from{" "}
                        <a href="https://www.upn.edu.pe/" target="_blank">
                            Universidad Privada del Norte
                        </a>, where I graduated with a 4.0 GPA. At Skolkovo's{" "}
                        <a
                            href="https://smiles.skoltech.ru/school-2020"
                            target="_blank"
                        >
                            SMILES 2020
                        </a>{" "}
                        summer school I placed in the top 10% of 2,000+
                        applicants and presented my work on Convolutional Neural
                        Networks for respiratory-condition detection. I'm
                        pursuing an MSc in Computer Science at the{" "}
                        <a href="https://www.london.ac.uk/" target="_blank">
                            University of London
                        </a>.
                    </p>
                    <p>
                        As a REPU Computer Science alum, I analyzed 80,000
                        COVID-19 texts with Gisella Bejarano in Arti Ramesh's lab
                        at Binghamton University, and we published a{" "}
                        <a
                            href="https://link.springer.com/chapter/10.1007/978-3-030-91434-9_18"
                            target="_blank"
                        >
                            paper
                        </a>{" "}
                        indexed in the{" "}
                        <a
                            href="https://pesquisa.bvsalud.org/global-literature-on-novel-coronavirus-2019-ncov/resource/pt/covidwho-1593151?lang=en"
                            target="_blank"
                        >
                            WHO COVID-19 Research Database
                        </a>.
                    </p>
                    <p>
                        Beyond the code, I do vocals in a band called{" "}
                        <a
                            href="https://pebeto.github.io/elmejorveranodemivida/"
                            target="_blank"
                        >
                            El mejor verano de mi vida
                        </a>{" "}
                        (The best summer of my life). We got counted in the fifth
                        wave of emo, and I'm proud of it. I also play Magic: The
                        Gathering and spend time with my two cats.
                    </p>
                </div>

                <h2
                    class="text-2xl font-semibold text-[var(--color-heading)] pt-4"
                >
                    Tech stack
                </h2>

                <div>
                    <dl class="space-y-3 text-sm">
                        <div class="flex flex-col sm:flex-row sm:gap-4">
                            <dt
                                class="font-semibold text-[var(--color-heading)] sm:w-36 shrink-0"
                            >
                                ML & LLMs
                            </dt>
                            <dd class="text-[var(--color-text-muted)]">
                                PyTorch, HF Transformers, vLLM, LangGraph,
                                LlamaIndex, MCP/FastMCP, LLaMA-Factory
                            </dd>
                        </div>
                        <div class="flex flex-col sm:flex-row sm:gap-4">
                            <dt
                                class="font-semibold text-[var(--color-heading)] sm:w-36 shrink-0"
                            >
                                Data & infra
                            </dt>
                            <dd class="text-[var(--color-text-muted)]">
                                Spark, Airflow, Databricks, AWS, GCP, Docker,
                                Kubernetes
                            </dd>
                        </div>
                        <div class="flex flex-col sm:flex-row sm:gap-4">
                            <dt
                                class="font-semibold text-[var(--color-heading)] sm:w-36 shrink-0"
                            >
                                Languages
                            </dt>
                            <dd class="text-[var(--color-text-muted)]">
                                Python, SQL, Julia, TypeScript, C++, CUDA
                            </dd>
                        </div>
                    </dl>
                    <p class="text-sm text-[var(--color-text-faint)] mt-4">
                        <a href="/resume.pdf" target="_blank"
                            >Full stack on my resume ↗</a
                        >
                    </p>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </main>
</Layout>
